Nature preserve workers in northwest China's Gansu Province have formulated a rescue plan to save giant pandas from food shortage caused by arrow bamboo flowering.
In Sichuan and Shaanxi provinces, two other habitats of giant pandas, arrow bamboo was found blooming.
The nature preserve, occupying about 220,000 hectares, has 102 giant pandas living wild.
The Baishuijiang State Nature Reserve is home to more than 100 giant pandas.
China has applied to the United Nations to make giant pandas' natural habitat in southwestern Sichuan province a world heritage area to help protect the endangered species.
